}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "1246-01000119-50U" and "USB-AC56 V1.4" appears to be silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. This adapter is using two ''[[Skyworks]] (SiGe)'' SE5003L1 High Power 802.11ac (5GHz) WLAN Power Amplifiers. :The other RFICs may be from [http://www.epic.com.tw/ ''Epicom'']..
The USB ID for this device is found in the driver set for [[Edimax EW-7822UAC]]. :''[[Realtek]]'' Linux driver set for the '''8812au''' states the manufactuer is ''[[Edimax]]''. <small> *'''Warning:''' The '''ASUS USB-AC56''' adapters sold in the EU do not support channels higher than 140 under Windows 10. There are no relevant settings to configure, so the only solution is to return the adapter. Adapters sold directly by Amazon (US) do not have this limitation. </small>
